Bug: several places in google-breakpad's Linux client assume things about
glibc that are no longer true on modern glibc:
 - <sys/ucontext.h> no longer exposes a `struct ucontext` tag (only the
   `ucontext_t` typedef survives), so code using `struct ucontext` fails
   with "field/argument has incomplete type" or "does not name a type".
 - glibc now declares its own extern tgkill(), conflicting with this
   file's own `static int tgkill(...)` syscall-wrapper definition.
 - SIGSTKSZ is no longer a compile-time int constant on modern glibc (it
   is computed at runtime via sysconf and is a `long`), so
   `std::max(8192, SIGSTKSZ)` fails to resolve (int vs long).
Point signal-context code at ucontext_t, rename the local tgkill wrapper
to avoid the glibc symbol clash, and make the std::max call type-correct.
